@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy";
}

<section class="hero-panel hero-panel-compact">
    <span class="eyebrow">Privacy And Scope</span>
    <h1>This capstone app remains fully local.</h1>
    <p class="lead mb-0">
        All data is stored in memory for the current session only, and the app uses local controllers and fragment endpoints instead of external services.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="card-grid">
    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>Local Data</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>No database is required.</li>
            <li>No external API is required.</li>
            <li>Tasks and reflections reset when the app stops.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>CORS And Swagger</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>CORS is enabled in development so the API can be called from different local origins when needed.</li>
            <li>Swagger UI is available in development for API discovery and testing.</li>
            <li>XML comments are enabled so endpoint descriptions appear in the documentation.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>
